          p Fulgurite, also referred to as <b>petrified lightning</b>, is a glass tube formed by lightning striking sand. It can be over an inch diameter and found up to 50 feet below the surface of the strike. 
            a(href="http://www.treasuremountainmining.com/servlet/the-template/articles/Page?article=fulgurite") (photo credit)

          p We considered calling these Fulgurite Talks, since we're preserving the lightning talk on the internets, topics can be deep and tubular, and some of the speakers seemed petrified! But no one could pronounce it and we decided to keep it simple and pithy.

  